    "One of the components that has largely been left out of building KGQA systems using LLMs, is the importance of ontologies.",
    "An ontology consists of classes, object properties, and datatype properties.",
    "An example of an ontology from the Spider4SPARQL dataset is shown in Figure 2.",
    "One of the key errors that KGQA systems make, is predicting triple patterns that do not exist or are in the wrong direction when connecting classes such as stadium and concert shown in Example 1.",
    "This challenge is specific to KGQA systems and does not apply to similar systems used for relational databases, such as text-to-SQL systems."
